# 15. あの日の想い

Bunny Plushie: Waaah...
Tsukasa: Hey, um, what's wrong? Why are you crying?
Tsukasa: Uh, why am I talking to a toy as if it were a person...
Bunny Plushie: *Sniff*... Bwaaah!
Tsukasa: Don't cry, don't cry! Hmm... Look! Watch this, I'll do a snazzy dance for you!
Bunny Plushie: Waaah!
Tsukasa: That only made it cry even more?! I guess there's nothing I can do...
Tsukasa: Hold on, there's something else I could try, maybe?
Bunny Plushie: Booohooo!
Tsukasa: Hey, hey! W-Wonderhoy! This is the Wonder Stage, a place fiilled with smiles♪
Bunny Plushie: Boo...huh?
Tsukasa: Err... This time I want you to join in! Ready? Wonderhoy!
Bunny Plushie: Wonder...boy?
Tsukasa: Close, but it's “hoy,” not “boy”! Reach up and wave with both hands like this!
Bunny Plushie: Wonderhoy!
Tsukasa: Ha ha ha! That's it! Now that you can do wonderhoy, you can consider yourself the prince's friend!
Bunny Plushie: What prince?
Tsukasa: Well, I'm the prince, of course! And that makes you my friend!
Bunny Plushie: Oh! We're friends! Prince, can we go on an adventure now?
Tsukasa: Um... H-Hey, don't pull my arm!
Tsukasa: Watch out, a storm's coming! Our boat's tiny, things are going to get rocky!
Bunny Plushie: You hold on tight too, Tsukasa!
Tsukasa: That's a powerful monster! How can we defeat it...
Bunny Plushie: I think this sword will work on it!
Tsukasa: Ha ha ha! That was a grand adventure! And somehow... It feels really nostalgic.
Bunny Plushie: Me too, Tsukasa.
Tsukasa: Hey, there's something written under your foot?
Tsukasa: “Saki”? Come to think of it, Saki used to have a bunny plushie, didn't she?
Tsukasa: Could you be...Saki's bunny?
Bunny Plushie: Saki and I used to play together lots!
Tsukasa: Actually, now that I think of it... You're not the only thing that's familiar around here...
Tsukasa: That's the tent I used for my very first original show. And there's the poster I made, with me as the play's hero... That steam train and those decorations are mine too!
Miku: Of course they are. This world is made from your feelings and memories!
Tsukasa: Miku and KAITO! Have you been watching me all this time?
KAITO: Yes. We were enjoying the show.
KAITO: You were dazzling, like a real star.
Tsukasa: What? It was just pretend play...
Miku: What matters is that you made our sad little friend happy again!
Tsukasa: I guess I did cheer it up... Wait a minute...
Little Saki: Tsukasa, why can't I go to school with everyone else?
Little Saki: I want to go to school and have fun with my friends...
Little Tsukasa: .....
Little Tsukasa: Neiiigh!
Little Saki: Huh?!
Little Tsukasa: I'm the defender of world peace! My name is Pegasusman!
Little Tsukasa: I'm going to punish the evil sickness that's been making you sad, Saki! Come out, show yourself! You're hiding from me?! Saki, the enemy is a coward!
Little Saki: Pffft... Hahahaha! Pegasusman? Who's that?
Little Saki: I want to know all about his adventures!
Tsukasa: I remember now...
Tsukasa: I did all that because I wanted to cheer up Saki...
Tsukasa: At that show we saw together, the one that made me want to become a star...
Tsukasa: I only decided to become a star because I wanted to be like the stars there, who made me and Saki so happy.
Tsukasa: But at some point I forgot about all that, and all I cared about was making successful shows and becoming a star...
Tsukasa: How could I have...
Robo-Nene: I hope our audience enjoys the play.
Rui: Well then. Let's work together to put on some unbeatable shows!
Emu: It's my dream to have people come to see a show here at this stage and love it!
Tsukasa: .....
Tsukasa: They're the real stars, not me...
KAITO: Tsukasa, you're one of them.
Tsukasa: Huh?
Miku: Yup! Your little performance earlier was stellar☆
Miku: It must have been because you remembered what really matters to you. And now that you have, you also have the power to make people smile again!
Tsukasa: But how can I make those guys happy again...
KAITO: I'm sure you can. Aren't you a future star that will bring joy to everyone?
Tsukasa: !!
Tsukasa: Haha...
Tsukasa: That's exactly who I am! Thank you for helping me remember.
Tsukasa: There's no one here. I guess that's no surprise.
Tsukasa: Argh! I can't stand around feeling sorry for myself! I've got to go look for them!
Tsukasa: Rui may be doing one of his shows somewhere in the park. I have no clue how to find Nene, but Rui can help with that...
Tsukasa: Hmm? Is that Emu over by the Ferris wheel?!
Tsukasa: Emu!
Emu: Oh, Tsukasa?
Tsukasa: Emu, I... About what happened yesterday...
Emu: Tsukasa, do you want to ride the Ferris wheel with me?
Tsukasa: Huh?
